EntityManager
--------------------

EntityManager is an interface present in the javax.persistence package.
It provides many methods; using them we can perform CRUD operations on the database tables.
By using the createEntityManager method of the EntityManagerFactory interface, we can create the instance of EntityManager.
We can create multiple EntityManager instances by using the same EntityManagerFactory instance to perform actions on a particular database.


EntityTransaction
-------------------

A transaction is a set of operations that either fail or succeed as a unit.
A database transaction consists of a set of SQL DML operations that are committed or rolled back as a single unit.
An object-level transaction is one in which a set of changes made to a set of objects are committed to the database as a single unit.
EntityTransaction interface provides important methods to handle transactions in JPA-based applications.


